-- Level 6: Reactive Relevance Changes
-- Tests that parameters can become relevant/irrelevant as user provides input
-- Formula: (switch AND option_a) OR (NOT switch AND option_b)
--
-- This is the if-then-else pattern: if switch then option_a else option_b
--
-- Scenario:
--   1. User sets switch=true
--      → option_a becomes relevant, option_b becomes irrelevant (grayed)
--   2. User fills in grayed option_b anyway (allowed!)
--      → System accepts it
--   3. User changes mind: switch=false
--      → option_b becomes relevant (un-grays), option_a becomes irrelevant
--      → System uses the option_b value user already provided!
--
-- Expected behaviors:
--   switch=true:  still needs option_a, option_b is don't-care
--   switch=false: still needs option_b, option_a is don't-care
--   switch=true, option_a=true:  determined True, option_b is don't-care
--   switch=false, option_b=true: determined True, option_a is don't-care
--
-- Key UX requirement:
--   Even when option_b is grayed (don't-care), user can input it
--   If user later changes switch, that input becomes relevant!

@export default Test reactive relevance changes
GIVEN
  @desc The switch that determines which branch to take
  switch IS A BOOLEAN
  @desc Option A - only relevant when switch is true
  option_a IS A BOOLEAN
  @desc Option B - only relevant when switch is false
  option_b IS A BOOLEAN
GIVETH A BOOLEAN
DECIDE `if-then-else result` IF (switch AND option_a) OR (NOT switch AND option_b)
